can use it for as long as it lasts. Again, that's up to the Twitter API. I'm not sure

00:27:18.859 --> 00:27:24.859
how long that lasts, but you only have to run steps one and two once, and you should

00:27:24.859 --> 00:27:30.859
only have to run step three periodically based on the API. Then you can run as many requests

